        P6.M1 — placeholder pricing rules (18 rows: 9 categories
        × 2 currencies = USD + ZWG).

        PLACEHOLDER VALUES — Munashe to override during P6.M2 or
        P6.M3 build with real rate cards before Phase 6 production
        deploy (P6.M12).

        Only the Sound (USD $50 / ZiG 500) and Visual (USD $80 /
        ZiG 800) values come from the spec; the rest are
        order-of-magnitude placeholders. Real rates land via the
        Configuration > Finance > Pricing Rules form once Munashe
        provides them.

        Standard bracket per rule:
            1-2 days   → multiplier 1.00 (full rate)
            3-7 days   → multiplier 0.80
            8-14 days  → multiplier 0.70
            15-∞ days  → multiplier 0.60 (open-ended tail)

        noupdate="1" — these are install-time seeds. Editing the
        bracket values in this XML afterwards will NOT reapply on
        -u; edits happen through the form view.
    -->
